	abstract = {Abstract
            
              Mercury dynamics in the process of litter decomposition is crucial to understanding the atmospheric mercury deposition to soils in the forest catchments. This work aimed to quantify mercury internal biogeochemical cycling and the fractionation process in a coniferous forest and a broad‐leaved forest in southwest China. Annual deposition fluxes of total mercury (THg) and methylmercury (MeHg) via litterfall were 40.5 and 0.10 μg/m
